# IRC

`#bcache` on `irc.oftc.net`.

Join in a web browser:
<https://webchat.oftc.net/?randomnick=1&channels=bcache&prompt=1>

<iframe src="https://webchat.oftc.net/?randomnick=1&channels=bcache&prompt=1" width="647" height="400"></iframe>

## Joining from Matrix

`#bcache` is bridged into Matrix via the official
[matrix-appservice-irc](https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-appservice-irc)
bridge run by the Matrix.org Foundation. Any Matrix client works — no
separate IRC client needed.

**Join:** `#_oftc_#bcache:matrix.org`

Matrix users appear in the IRC channel with a `[m]` suffix on their
nick. Multi-homeserver: your homeserver MXID prefix shows up in the
IRC user's realname (e.g. `org.matrix:nickname`, `de.tnxip:nickname`).

**Bridge bot:** `@oftc-irc:matrix.org`

### Reporting bridge problems

Bridge issues (dropped messages, missing relays, lost connections,
reconnect failures) aren't a bcachefs problem; the bcachefs maintainers
can't fix them. Report to the bridge operators:

* Support room: [`#irc:matrix.org`](https://matrix.to/#/#irc:matrix.org)
* Bug tracker: <https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-appservice-irc>

### Known limitations

OFTC doesn't support SASL, so when the bridge reconnects you may need
to manually `REGAIN` your nickname from NickServ. Tracked upstream as
[matrix-appservice-irc#1483](https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-appservice-irc/issues/1483).
